The paper is about improving recommendation performance by integrating different types of information, which is a common topic in information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of meta path based similarity measure and matrix factorization also suggests a focus on network analysis and data mining, which are often associated with sub-categories such as cs.SI and cs.DB. Finally, the paper's emphasis on attribute information and regularization frameworks aligns with research in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
